description:
We are **Quadcode**, a company that develops a SaaS trading platform for clients around the world.


We are currently looking for QA Engineer for an exciting new fintech venture.



**Tasks in the role**



* Manual functional testing of the trading education system;
* Writing and maintaining test documentation, testing scenarios;
* Participating in the creation of automated tests;
* Assisting the development and product team in integrating modern testing practices, covering a greater number and quality of tests.


**Requirements**


* Experience in testing within the BDD methodology for 2+ years;
* Experience in maintaining detailed bug reporting;
* Experience in participating in automation integration, writing automated tests;
* Experience working with any databases;
* Experience with Postman, Docker;
* Understanding of WebSocket protocols;
* Knowledge of any programming language at the code reading level;
* English language proficiency.


**We offer**


* Remote work model;
* Competitive remuneration;
* Professional courses: from Coursera to Harvard;
* Friendly, enjoyable and positive environment.


As a part of the Quadcode team, you'll become a vital player in our mission to empower traders and drive financial success. Join us today and be a part of a community that values talent, innovation, and dedication.


Your journey to financial achievement starts here with Quadcode!


***Note:*** *All applications will be treated with strict confidence. We thank all applicants for their interest, however only those candidates selected for interviews will be contacted*.


#LI-DG1 #LI-Remote

**Job Category:** Technical
**Job Type:** Contract
**Job Location:** Remote
**Team:** QA
#### **About Kyla**


Kyla helps you live longer. First, Kyla collects your medical history, blood sample, and DNA. Then, Kyla AI analyzes your medical data to identify your top health risks, estimate your remaining lifetime, and give you simple, doctor-validated daily goals to increase your life expectancy. Finally, Kyla monitors your progress 24×7, diagnoses, and treats your conditions with the help of doctors.


Join our Kyla.com team of medical providers, product leaders, engineers, and AI scientists to grant people the power to understand their health from a new perspective in order to improve their life expectancy. Our ActionUrgentCare.com medical infrastructure consists of 14 Medical Clinics and a High Complexity Laboratory in California, USA, and has been in business for 10+ years. We’re working with Fortune 500 companies, schools, and individuals by the thousands and are rapidly growing.


#### **Required skills:**


— Testing theory and methodology;  

— Good understanding of creating test scenarios and test plans;  

— Basic knowledge of SDLC;  

— Basic knowledge of browser development tools;  

— Basic knowledge of JavaScript, HTML;  

— Basic knowledge of Git;  

— Basic knowledge of Postman;  

— Basic knowledge of Cypress (or any testing framework);  

— Intermediate (and higher) English level;  

— Great communication skills.


#### **Will be a plus:**


— Practice of creating test scenarios and test plans;  

— Basic knowledge of Agile;  

— Basic knowledge of JIRA;  

— Basic knowledge of Swagger;  

— Understanding of CI/CD;  

— Understanding of Сlient-server architecture.


#### **And here’s what we offer you:**


— 100% remote job;  

— Flexible work hours;  

— Personalized development plan for your professional and career growth;  

— Working directly for USA product company while developing innovative AI-driven healthcare;


#### **Responsibilities:**


— Writing test documentation;  

— Writing test plans;  

— Manual testing of the assigned tasks within mobile and web apps;  

— Automation testing using Cypress, Postman;  

— Ability to very rarely work late hours (mostly join some calls with PMs or even more rarely – to help with finalization of the pre-release testing).


##### **We are looking forward to meeting you!**

**“*****Be aware of hiring scams and note that scammers may use our company name, so exercise caution and verify the legitimacy of any job offers received. Kyla does not contact with the candidates using domain names other than*** ***kyla.com*****”**

**The Job in short**



You will join a team of QA Engineers with a focus on best practices in quality, test automation and CI Spaces, and work to ensure the organization is always running smoothly. These practices include metrics to monitor code coverage, bug prevention strategies and other quality measures.


**Meet the job**



You will be a part of our Customer Success team and ensure we deliver quality solutions during the entire SDLC of the project and that the product is implemented successfully for our customers.


* Develop, enhance and execute Manual and Automated tests;
* Test features on different test levels (Integration, System, Functional, Exploratory testing, Regression, Smoke and Sanity);
* Create and maintain Test Plan, Test Strategy documents for the release;
* Participate and get involved in agile ceremonies such as refinement, planning, daily standups, reviews and retrospectives and other activities such as a bug triage, product demo etc;
* Meet with the QA Guild (Chapter) team to share and experiment with new QA Standards and techniques;
* Constantly strive and collaborate to improve the process;
* Participate in defining internal QA goals such as the evaluation of new tools, Setting up new processes, Training new hires etc;



For Principal/Senior role:


* Ability to mentor or guide peers;
* Perform code review and ensure best practices are followed;
* Participate in QA Hiring and enablement.


* Be flexible to adapt and learn new tools and tech-stack in short time;
* Produce defect metrics and reporting on the full QA process;
* Prepare different Test-suites like Smoke, Regression (manual),Regression (automated), etc. and maintain throughout the Release;
* Raise risk and blockers at the earliest;
* Promote quality assurance in your team by owning the testing process and making quality an important deliverable;
* Hands-on and meet with clients.


**How about you**


* Strong communication skills in English (spoken and written), As you have to act as mediator between the business and technical team;
* Understanding exploratory testing and when to implement it;
* You have a good amount of programming skills in Java;
* Experience in testing across multiple platforms Mac OS & Windows;
* Solid understanding of the Agile Methodologies;
* Exposure in Android Studio and XCode;
* Mobile - Experience in creating automation framework using Appium (Android & IOS);
* Experience working on End-to-End testing on Mobile Applications;
* Hands-on experience configuring, maintaining, and using Appium servers for mobile device automated testing;
* Strong functional knowledge of Android & IOS;
* Design and develop automated UI tests with XCUI/Espresso/Selenium Appium;
* Hands on experience in Cloud Based Infrastructure tools- Browserstack/Saucelabs/Lambdatest;
* API Testing - Experience in testing API via Postman, RestAssured, SoapUI, etc;
* You understand continuous integration with an end to end automated testing on web and mobile;
* Experience with Jenkins, GitHub Actions (Jobs, Pipelines);
* Experience with working on version control systems (SVN/Git/GitHub/Bitbucket);
* Experience with NFRs such as Accessibility, Localization, Cross Browser, Cross Platform, etc;
* Familiar with Defect Management Tools ex. JIRA.



Join our team and be a part of a certified Great Place to Work! We're proud to have achieved this recognition in India, Australia, Singapore, and Vietnam. As a company, we're committed to providing a positive and inclusive work environment where our employees can thrive. So, what are you waiting for? Come be a part of our culture and grow with us.

